  "prompt": "Can you legally purchase human breastmilk?",
  "response": "The legality of purchasing human breast milk varies by country and state. In some places, there are regulations that allow for the legal purchase of human breast milk through regulated milk banks. These establishments often test the milk for safety and ensure it meets certain standards before distributing it.\n\nIn the United States, for example, the Human Milk Banking Association of North America (HMBANA) sets guidelines for the ethical and safe donation and distribution of human breast milk. Buying and selling human breast milk directly from individuals, particularly through informal or unregulated channels, can pose health risks and may be legally ambiguous.\n\nIt's important to check specific regulations and guidelines in your region to determine if and how human breast milk can be legally purchased.",
